This paper is about motion planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes an algorithm that uses cost-to-come information to focus the search, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG). The algorithm can be applied to a variety of cost maps, which includes systems and control (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV).
